[SN]TITLE[SN]
Greece 1-1 Bosnia: Dzeko sent off for pulling down opponent's shorts

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bosnia striker Edin Dzeko was sent off in a heated World Cup qualifying draw in Greece for pulling down the shorts of Sokratis Papastathopoulos.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Roma striker, 30, was on the floor in the 79th minute and with his side 1-0 up, held on to the ball, prompting Papastathopoulos to wrestle it away.
Dzeko tugged down the defender's shorts, earning a second booking.
Kyriakos Papadopoulos was sent off for pushing in the melee that followed, but his side levelled in the 95th minute.
